Complete and well-aligned chords / intermediate with split chords and suggestions for playable voicings / tab for intro melody.
Different cadences and other harmonic changes.
To Play this in the song's originally recorded key (E), just add a capo on the 4th fret and use these same chords in that position.
Not so easy to play those chords.

The chords are unusual but accurate so you must use the ones that are outlined at the start, using any other variations won't sound right. No capo is needed and tuning is a Half-Step Down (Eb tuning).
